posts.title: ****  Hard pass for me on "The Stargate Project"  ****
posts.content:
Trump thinks it's about bringing money and jobs into the US.

I see it as a giant invasion of privacy and over-reach headed by never-Trumper Sam Altman and Tech guru Larry Ellison. It will be a huge money pit and endless abuse of power by a giant bureaucracy that will initially have access to every American's health records. Easily accessible by the intelligence community to blackmail anyone in power or use the information to influence elections and health recommendations. So much power in the hands of so few should never be made available for the purpose of "good intentions". It is the sad state of human nature to abuse such a vast concentrated resource.

mRNA is an extremely dangerous experimental use that changes a person's DNA and should be cautiously approached over long term study. Not by artificial intelligence snap decisions.

We have already seen the impact the government pushed mRNA "vaccinations" have had on millions of people's health resulting in diminished well being and death. We have seen the impact that government restricted drugs like Ivermectin and Hydroxychloroquine had on the positive results on people with flu, cancer and other unhealthy situations that have been negatively compromised by government propaganda in order to use "Emergency Use" experimental drugs to create Billions of dollars in profit for pharma companies and private individuals, including politicians and heads of "government" agencies.

The Stargate Project is not limited to medical research but expands to ALL uses of A.I. including intelligence gathering and decision making on American citizens and social engineering on an incredibly huge and invasive scale. If you have seen the fake photos and videos produced by AI, then you have a small glimpse of the abuse of power granted by a technology that can influence ALL aspects of society in the hands of a future unelected and unaccountable bureaucratic corporation (think Google, Microsoft, Facebook, Mainstream Media) after the Communists reclaim their power over the next 10-20 years. The government WILL join forces in the future as they have in the past for money and power. It is just too tempting.

The miracles produced by Silicon Valley over the past 50 years were by small individual companies operating on shoestring budgets until they proved themselves to the tightly controlled allocation of funds from VC firms, not huge pits of unlimited money sanctioned by unknown corporate entities. The (questionable) $500 Billion promised to one large technocratic social-engineering bureaucracy is a disaster waiting to happen both financially and technologically. It is backwards from the historical ways companies have failed or succeeded in the past. Stargate, like all monopolistic bureaucracies, has no competition and hence, no motivation to develop, only to consume and expand (like the NSA).

I truly do not think that this effort will "Make America Great Again". The money could be spent in many different ways to develop AI for needed goods and services. To develop and maintain highway infrastructure, power grid, satellite and ground sourced communications, water and sanitation, landfills, trucking, railroads, airlines, and probably dozens more areas by hundreds of individual companies competing against each other for the good of actual consumers.
